<div id="node-806" class="node node-expert">


  <h2><a href="../../expert/clayton-munnings" title="Clayton Munnings">Clayton Munnings</a></h2>

  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Munnings2_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="120" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>Clayton Munnings is a Research Associate at Resources for the Future, a non-partisan think tank based in Washington DC. Clayton‚Äôs research focuses on the use of market-based instruments to reduce carbon emissions in developed and developing countries, including China. Clayton holds a BS in Science of Natural and Environmental Systems with a concentration in Environmental and Resource Economics from Cornell University.</p>
<div class="field field-type-text field-field-contact-info">
      <div class="field-label">Contact Info:&nbsp;</div>
