<div id="node-676" class="node node-library">


  <h2><a href="../../library/second-national-communication-climate-change-peoples-republic-china" title="Second National Communication on Climate Change of the People&#039;s Republic of China">Second National Communication on Climate Change of the People&#039;s Republic of China</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by National Development and Reform Commission of the People&amp;#039;s Republic of China on Dec 8, 2012</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-library-file">
      <div class="field-label">Library File:&nbsp;</div>
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../../files/chinainfo/chnnc2e.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=3169806">chnnc2e.pdf</a></div>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>China submitted its <a href="http://unfccc.int/essential_background/library/items/3599.php?rec=j&amp;priref=7666#beg">&#8220;Second National Communication on Climate Change of the People&#8217;s Republic of China&#8221;</a> to the UNFCCC in November 2012. The Communication contains a national greenhouse gas inventory of China&#8217;s emissions in 2005, and descriptions of the impacts of climate change in China and China&#8217;s policies and actions on climate change mitigation.</p>
  </div>
<div class="clear-block">
    	<div class="readmore"> <a href="../../library/second-national-communication-climate-change-peoples-republic-china">Read more</a> </div>
  </div>

